            "wexRAR+": { short: "wexRAR+ is a composite index (where 100 represents average compared to what is available to you based on your budget and needs) that estimates the expected audience retention of a creator’s sponsored content above a readily available alternative, adjusted for niche and brand alignment, production and aesthetic compatibility, audience demographics, audience authenticity, and the financial and operational constraints of the sponsoring organization. The metric discounts inflated reach driven by bots, paid views, or low-quality traffic that does not generate sustained attention, prioritizing organic retention as the primary indicator of real impact and value." + dynamicNote, long: "wexRAR+ is an index-based metric (where 100 represents average compared to what is available to you based on your budget and needs) that estimates the expected audience retention of a creator’s sponsored content above or below a readily available alternative, adjusted for niche alignment, production and aesthetic compatibility, audience demographics, financial feasibility, negotiating context, and audience authenticity.\n\nThe metric is designed to evaluate not who is largest, but who is most likely to sustain attention and deliver meaningful impact given the specific constraints and objectives of a nonprofit or mission-driven organization.\n\nwexRAR+ accounts for the degree of niche correlation between the creator and the organization, reducing expected retention when audiences are weakly correlated or when collaborations are likely to feel generic or inauthentic. It incorporates visual and production alignment, including color palette, cinematography, and stylistic appeal to the organization’s primary demographics, recognizing that mismatched aesthetic language can materially reduce retention even when reach is high.\n\nThe metric integrates audience demographic composition, including age distribution and psychographic compatibility, to better estimate whether viewers are likely to meaningfully engage with and remain attentive to the content. It further adjusts for organizational fiscal context, weighing creator affordability, demand, travel and production costs, time requirements, and relative negotiating power to prevent overvaluing creators whose costs scale faster than expected retention.\n\nwexRAR+ also includes an audience authenticity and retention-quality adjustment, discounting expected performance when follower behavior suggests a significant presence of bots, automated traffic, or low-intent audiences. Because inauthentic followers do not generate organic retention, the metric distinguishes between paid or inflated views and genuine, sustained watch time, ensuring that apparent scale does not outweigh real attention.\n\nIn aggregate, wexRAR+ provides a context-aware estimate of how much retention a creator is expected to generate relative to a replacement-level option, enabling more efficient, realistic, and impact-driven creator selection under real-world budgetary and operational constraints.\n\nImportant: wexRAR+ is not a standard formula; it has a base formula that we are collecting data on to improve its accuracy relating to its different modifiers, so please do not use that statistic as an end-all-be-all." + dynamicNote },
